// Draft Poker
// 
// Each hand is assigned a point value (pair = 3, full house = 8, etc.)
// 
// Draw 7 cards in a draft style format
// Gain points based on the hand you drafted
// Play a number of rounds (say 16)
// Add up points from across all rounds
// Winner is whoever had the most combined points
// 
// Some cards that are not draftable this round are shown to everyone
// 
// The 3rd, 5th and 6th card drafted by each player are added to the shown cards
// 
// Draft picks come in groups of 4
// the groups of 4 are chosen randomly from this round's draftable cards
// 
// Point values
// Straight flush: 72,000 * highest card // 72000:1
// Four of a kind: 4,200 * card // 4200:1
// Full House: 700 ((triple card * 4/5) + (pair card * 1/5)) // 700:1
// Flush: 500 * highest card // 500:1
// Straight: 250 * highest card // 250:1
// Three of a kind: 50 * card value // 50:1
// Two pair: 10 * (sum of card values) // 20:1
// One pair: 2 * card value // 2:1(ish)
// Nothing: 1 // 1:1
// 
// 
// 
// 2 player drafts (14 total cards)
// show 20 cards to everyone
// 
// 
// 
// 4 player drafts (28 total cards)
// show 10 cards to everyone
// 
// 
// 
// 6 player drafts (42 total cards)
// show 5 cards to everyone
// 
// 
// 
// 
